 like it cold: Biocatalysis at low temperatures (2004) FEMS Microbiol Rev, 28, pp. 25-42; Griffiths, B.S., Donn, S., Neilson, R., Daniell, T.J., Molecular sequencing and morphological analysis of a nematode community (2006) Appl Soil Ecol, 32, pp. 325-337; Harris, J.M., Tibbles, B.J., Factors affecting bacterial productivity in soils on isolated inland nunataks in continental Antarctica (1997) Microb Ecol, 33, pp. 106-123; Heuer, H., Krsek, M., Baker, P., Smalla, K., Wellington, E., Analysis of actinomycete communities by specific amplification of genes encoding 16S rRNA and gel-electrophoretic separation in denaturing gradients (1997) Appl Environ Microbiol, 63, pp. 3233-3241; Houghton, J.T., Ding, Y., Griggs, D.J., Noguer, M., van der Linden, P.J., Dai, X., Maskell, K., Johnson, C.A., (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis. Contribution of Working Group I to the Third Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK; Kaštovská, K., Elster, J., Stibal, M., Šantrů čková, H., Microbial assemblages in soil microbial succession after glacial retreat in Svalbard (high Arctic) (2005) Microb Ecol, 50, pp. 396-407; Kennedy, A.D., Water as a limiting factor in the Antarctic terrestrial environment: A biogeographical synthesis (1993) Arct Alp Res, 25, pp. 308-315; Kerry, E., Effects of temperature on growth-rates of fungi from sub-antarctic Macquarie Island and Casey, Antarctica (1990) Polar Biol, 10, pp. 293-299; Kowalchuk, G.A., Buma, D.S., de Boer, W., Klinkhamer, P.G.L., van Veen, J.A., Effects of above-ground plant species composition and diversity on the diversity of soil-borne microorganisms (2002) Antonie Van Leeuwenhoek, 81, pp. 509-520; Lawley, B., Ripley, S., Bridge, P., Convey, P., Molecular analysis of geographic patterns of eukaryotic diversity in Antarctic soils (2004) Appl Environ Microbiol, 70, pp. 5963-5972; Leckie, S.E., Prescott, C.E., Grayston, S.J., Neufeld, J.D., Mohn, W.W., Compa